<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911210-0008</DOCNO><DOCID>911210-0008.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Novell Inc.:   Profit Rose 55% in Quarter   Bolstered by NetWare Sales</HL><DATE>12/10/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   NOVL</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)UTAH (UT)</RE><LP>   Novell Inc. posted a 55% increase in fiscal fourth-quarterearnings to $50.6 million, or 34 cents a share, up from $32.6million, or 23 cents a share, a year earlier.   Sales for the quarter ended Oct. 26 rose 33% to $187.2million from $140.5 million.</LP><TEXT>   The Provo, Utah, computer systems software concernattributed the strong performance to robust sales of its newversions of NetWare software, including the first Japaneselanguage version, which went on the market last summer.NetWare links desktop computers to networks.   For the year, Novell said earnings leaped 72% to $162.5million, or $1.10 a share, from $94.3 million, or 68 cents ashare, a year earlier. Sales rose 29% to $640.1 million from$497.5 million.   Novell said it had more than $300 million in sales ofNetWare software, and network operating system software salesaccounted for roughly 80% of its revenue.</TEXT></DOC>